$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-6 flex items-center gap-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-[#d4af37]/20 border border-[#d4af37]/30 flex items-center justify-center\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-bold text-[#d4af37] font-serif\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"H\\\"}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm font-semibold text-white font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hakeem Lesolang\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xs text-[#718096] font-sans\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hypnotherapist \\u0026 Peak Performance Coach\\\"}]]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-16 h-px bg-[#d4af37]/30 mb-12\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-custom\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"0\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Every couple I work with says they want more love. More passion. More connection. More of that feeling they had at the beginning.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"2\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"And I understand that. I do. But what their nervous systems are actually asking for — what the research consistently points to as the foundation of everything else — is something more fundamental.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"4\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Safety.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"6\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Not physical safety (though that matters enormously). Emotional safety. The felt sense that you can be fully yourself with this person — your needs, your fears, your imperfections, your history — and not be punished, abandoned, or diminished for it.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"8\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Hierarchy of Relationship Needs\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"10\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Just as Maslow proposed a hierarchy of human needs — with physiological safety at the base and self-actualisation at the top — there is a hierarchy of relationship needs. And emotional safety is the foundation.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"12\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Without emotional safety, you cannot have vulnerability. Without vulnerability, you cannot have intimacy. Without intimacy, you cannot have passion. Without passion, you cannot have the deeply alive, fully expressed partnership that most people are actually seeking.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"14\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Everyone wants the top of the pyramid. Nobody wants to build the base. That's the problem.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"16\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"What Emotional Safety Actually Is (And Isn't)\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"18\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Emotional safety is not the absence of conflict. It's not agreeing on everything. It's not walking on eggshells or avoiding difficult truths to keep the peace. That's not safety — that's fear wearing a mask.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"20\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Emotional safety is the confidence that:\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"26\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eI can express my needs without being mocked or dismissed.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003cbr /\\u003e- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eI can make mistakes without being defined by them.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003cbr /\\u003e- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eI can say \\\\\\\"this hurt me\\\\\\\" without being punished for having feelings.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003cbr /\\u003e- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eI can be imperfect without losing your love.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003cbr /\\u003e- \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eMy partner's response to my vulnerability will be care, not contempt.\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"28\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Dr. Sue Johnson describes this as the core question of every attachment bond: \\\\\\\"Are you there for me?\\\\\\\" Not \\\\\\\"Do you love me?\\\\\\\" — that's too abstract. \\\\\\\"Are you \\u003cem class=\\\\\\\"text-[#d4af37]/80\\\\\\\"\\u003ethere\\u003c/em\\u003e for me? When I'm scared. When I'm hurt. When I'm failing. When I need you most. Will you turn toward me?\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"30\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"When the answer is consistently yes, the nervous system settles into a state of felt security. And from that security, everything else becomes possible — deeper conversations, better sex, more playfulness, greater resilience during hardship, and the kind of trust that allows both partners to grow without growing apart.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"32\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Neuroscience of Safety\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"34\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Your brain has a surveillance system running 24/7, scanning your environment for cues of safety and danger. Dr. Stephen Porges calls this \\\\\\\"neuroception\\\\\\\" — the subconscious detection of threat or safety that occurs below the level of conscious awareness.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"36\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Your neuroception is always reading your partner. Their tone of voice. Their facial micro-expressions. The timing of their responses. The warmth or coldness in their eyes. All of this data is processed by the temporal cortex and fed to the amygdala in milliseconds, generating a felt sense of \\\\\\\"safe\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"not safe\\\\\\\" before your conscious mind has formed a single thought.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"38\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This is why your partner can say the \\\\\\\"right\\\\\\\" words in the wrong tone and it still feels terrible. Because your neuroception isn't listening to the content. It's reading the music. And the music is everything.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"40\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"When your neuroception detects safety — through warm prosody, soft eye contact, open body language, and responsive engagement — your ventral vagal system activates. Heart rate settles. Breathing deepens. The social engagement system comes online. You become capable of curiosity, empathy, playfulness, and vulnerability.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"42\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"When your neuroception detects threat — through harsh tone, averted gaze, dismissive body language, or emotional withdrawal — your sympathetic system activates. Fight or flight. And if the threat feels inescapable, you drop into dorsal vagal shutdown. Freeze. Disconnect. Go numb.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"44\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eYour partner's behaviour is constantly calibrating your nervous system.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Every interaction is either building safety or eroding it. There is no neutral.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"46\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Why \\\\\\\"Just Be Vulnerable\\\\\\\" Is Terrible Advice\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"48\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The self-help world loves to tell people to \\\\\\\"be vulnerable.\\\\\\\" Open up. Share your feelings. Let your walls down.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"50\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"This is well-intentioned and potentially dangerous.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"52\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"Vulnerability without safety is not brave — it's reckless. If you open up to a partner who responds with contempt, dismissal, or weaponised knowledge (\\\\\\\"You told me you were insecure about this, and now I can see why\\\\\\\"), you haven't built intimacy. You've been injured. And your nervous system will encode that injury as evidence that vulnerability is dangerous.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"54\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"The sequence must be: \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003esafety first, then vulnerability.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Not the other way around.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"56\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In my practice, I never ask a client to be vulnerable until I've assessed the safety of the container they're being vulnerable in. Is the partner capable of receiving the vulnerability? Are they regulated enough? Do they have the empathy resources? If not, we build that capacity first. Because premature vulnerability in an unsafe container doesn't heal — it retraumatises.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"58\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"How to Build Safety (The Concrete Practices)\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"60\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e1. Respond to bids with presence.\\u003c/strong\\u003e When your partner says \\\\\\\"look at this\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"listen to this\\\\\\\" or \\\\\\\"I had a hard day,\\\\\\\" stop what you're doing. Turn your body toward them. Make eye contact. This is not about the content of their bid. It's about communicating: \\\\\\\"You have my attention. You matter.\\\\\\\"\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"62\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e2. Regulate before you respond.\\u003c/strong\\u003e If your partner shares something that triggers you — a complaint, a need, a criticism — take a breath before responding. Your first response from activation will almost certainly be defensive. Your response after three conscious breaths will be closer to what the relationship actually needs.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"64\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e3. Validate before you problem-solve.\\u003c/strong\\u003e \\\\\\\"I hear you. That sounds really hard.\\\\\\\" That's it. That's the practice. Most people skip straight to fixing, advising, or defending. But the nervous system doesn't need a solution. It needs to feel felt.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"66\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e4. Keep confidences sacred.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Nothing destroys safety faster than having your vulnerable disclosures used against you — whether in an argument, in front of friends, or through passive-aggressive references. What is shared in vulnerability must be held with reverence. Period.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"68\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e5. Repair quickly after rupture.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Ruptures are inevitable. Even the safest relationships have moments of disconnection, misattunement, or hurt. What matters is the speed and quality of repair. \\\\\\\"I see that hurt you. I'm sorry. Can we talk about it?\\\\\\\" This teaches the nervous system that rupture is not permanent — that the bond can absorb conflict and come back stronger.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"70\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003e6. Be consistent over time.\\u003c/strong\\u003e Safety is not built in a single conversation. It's built through hundreds of repeated interactions that all communicate the same message: \\\\\\\"I am here. I am not going anywhere. You can count on me.\\\\\\\" Consistency is the neurological language of trust.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"72\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Hypnotherapy of Safety\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"74\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In deep trance work, I often guide clients to access their earliest experience of safety — or, more often, the absence of it. Many adults have never felt truly safe with another person. Their childhood didn't offer it. Their previous relationships didn't offer it. And so their nervous system has no reference point for what safety feels like.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"76\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"In hypnotherapy, we can create that reference point. Through guided imagery, somatic resourcing, and subconscious installation, we help the client's nervous system experience — often for the first time — what it feels like to be held, seen, and safe. This internal experience then becomes the template against which all future relational experiences are measured.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"78\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"It's not cognitive. It's not intellectual. It's felt. And once the nervous system has felt it, it begins to seek it, recognise it, and allow it in — including from a partner who has been offering it all along but couldn't get past the walls.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",\\\"80\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-2xl font-bold text-white font-serif mt-12 mb-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"The Invitation\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"82\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"If you take nothing else from this piece, take this: \\u003cstrong class=\\\\\\\"text-white font-semibold\\\\\\\"\\u003eyour relationship does not need more love. It needs more safety.\\u003c/strong\\u003e And safety is not a feeling you wait for. It's a practice you build. One interaction at a time. One repair at a time. One six-second kiss at a time.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"84\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"When you build safety, love doesn't just survive. It transforms. It becomes the kind of love that can hold conflict without crumbling. The kind that can absorb imperfection without withdrawing. The kind that makes both partners braver, softer, and more fully alive.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"86\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"That's not a fairy tale. That's neuroscience. That's attachment theory. That's the uncommon practice.\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",\\\"88\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[#cbd5e0] font-sans leading-[1.85] mb-6 text-base\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"And it's available to you. Starting now.\\\"}}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L16\\\",null,{\\\"title\\\":\\\"You Don't Need More Love. You Need More Safety.\\\",\\\"slug\\\":\\\"you-dont-need-more-love-you-need-more-safety\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L17\\\",null,{}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-16 rounded-2xl border border-[#d4af37]/30 bg-gradient-to-b from-[#d4af37]/10 to-transparent p-8 text-center\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h3\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold text-white font-serif\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Ready to talk about what you just read?\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-2 text-sm text-[#a0aec0] font-sans max-w-md mx-auto\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Book a free discovery call with Hakeem Lesolang. No pressure. No pitch. Just an honest conversation about where you are and where you want to be.\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"a\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://calendly.com/folasessions/discovery-call\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-6 inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-[#d4af37] text-[#1a365d] px-6 py-3 rounded-xl text-sm font-bold font-sans hover:bg-[#e4bf47] transition-all hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-[#d4af37]/20\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Book Your Free Discovery Call\\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"svg\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-4 h-4\\\",\\\"fill\\\":\\\"none\\\",\\\"viewBox\\\":\\\"0 0 24 24\\\",\\\"stroke\\\":\\\"currentColor\\\",\\\"strokeWidth\\\":2.5,\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"path\\\",null,{\\\"strokeLinecap\\\":\\\"round\\\",\\\"strokeLinejoin\\\":\\\"round\\\",\\\"d\\\":\\\"M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6\\\"}]}]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"w-full h-px bg-white/10 my-16\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\